    <stitle>RADIATOR SHUTTERS - OPERATION - SHUTTERS ON VEHICLES WITH VISCOUS FAN DRIVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="2">
        <title>SHUTTERS ON VEHICLES WITH VISCOUS FAN DRIVE</title>
        <para>On a vehicle equipped with a viscous fan drive, the shutters must ALWAYS BE OPEN BEFORE the fan drive
            engages. Refer to GROUP 12-ENGINE, VISCOUS FAN DRIVE in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual and to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1200507">Figure 7</hotlnk>and
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1200508">Figure 8</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1200507" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1200507" filename="../figg12/G1200507.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 7. Air-Controlled Shutters With Viscous Fan Drive</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. RADIATOR SHUTTER OVERRIDE PRESSURE SWITCH (N/C; USED WITH A/C)</callout1>
                <callout1>2. ROUTING WITHOUT A/C</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SHUTTER CONTROL SOLENOID #3 PORT (N/O; DO NOT PLUG)</callout1>
                <callout1>4. SHUTTER CONTROL SOLENOID #1 PORT (N/C; RED DOT)</callout1>
                <callout1>5. SHUTTER CONTROL SOLENOID #2 PORT (COM)</callout1>
                <callout1>6. SHUTTER CONTROL AIR SOLENOID</callout1>
                <callout1>7. PRESSURIZED SUPPLY AIR LINE</callout1>
                <callout1>8. AIR COMPRESSOR GOVERNOR PORT</callout1>
                <callout1>9. SHUTTER THERMAL SWITCH (N/C)</callout1>
                <callout1>10. ENGINE</callout1>
                <callout1>11. FAN</callout1>
                <callout1>12. VISCOUS DRIVE</callout1>
                <callout1>13. RADIATOR</callout1>
                <callout1>14. SHUTTER ASSEMBLY (REQUIRES AIR TO CLOSE VANES)</callout1>
                <callout1>15. CONTROL CYLINDER ON SHUTTERS</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1200508" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1200508" filename="../figg12/G1200508.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 8. Hydraulic-Controlled Shutters With Viscous Fan Drive</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. RADIATOR SHUTTER OVERRIDE PRESSURE SWITCH (N/C; USED WITH A/C)</callout1>
                <callout1>2. ROUTING WITHOUT A/C</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SHUTTER CONTROL SOLENOID HYDRAULIC OUTLET PORT</callout1>
                <callout1>4. SHUTTER CONTROL HYDRAULIC SOLENOID</callout1>
                <callout1>5. HYDRAULIC RETURN LINE</callout1>
                <callout1>6. HYDRAULIC SUPPLY LINE</callout1>
                <callout1>7. SHUTTER THERMAL SWITCH (N/C)</callout1>
                <callout1>8. ENGINE</callout1>
                <callout1>9. FAN</callout1>
                <callout1>10. VISCOUS DRIVE</callout1>
                <callout1>11. RADIATOR</callout1>
                <callout1>12. SHUTTER ASSEMBLY (REQUIRES OIL TO CLOSE VANES)</callout1>
                <callout1>13. CONTROL CYLINDER ON SHUTTERS</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
